{
  "stem": "13096.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Is that because we were taking you to the showers and this and that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were trying to speak to them in German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they couldn't believe what they were talking about.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is, it was on the 25th of January, 1945.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after that, in the history books and the magazine and all these things we heard about, it was the time that the Allied sent an ultimatum to the German people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "According to the-- to the stories of the magazine and the stories in the newspaper, it was only at that time the Allied knew about the crematorium, about the gas chamber, about all the things.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they say they didn't knew a thing before.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So only at that time, they knew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they send, you know, like you say, a warning to the Germans for whoever one Jew you will kill in those chambers, we are going to kill 10 Germans in our possession.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because at the time, the Germans were already losing the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were many, many thousands of prisoners in the hands of the Allies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now, these people, these Germans, to avoid, you know, their people to be killed, they stopped the killing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why they say it doesn't exist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the girls say, but what about those files going around?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Say, this is just the ovens that they're baking bread for tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it wasn't true.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, you know they stop.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That very moment, they stop.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And according to what we heard later on, that very same night they-- they blew away all the crematorium, all the gas chambers and all this, they were in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
